<subSubSection id="C7FB3F4C728D94189475173B743CBEE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="80CDECCF6BFC445AB0315B929FBC4578" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="20EA1DE5C0E8CE3A9DBF6AEC0E1BAB31" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemic to NE Brazil, growing in scrub around rock outcrops principally on or near the Serra de 
<normalizedToken id="13C3BEA2C899E7E5BD36C13F0829EF0E" originalValue="Carajás">Carajas</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E899DFDEBB5269DF67F1961795DA3D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="9DA7451072F38DC3DC02645C8567FF63" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
BRAZIL. 
<normalizedToken id="628578F3A0924D98FB42F399EDAC59E3" originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Serra de 
<normalizedToken id="CBA64C5353D3A81E909867CA2FBF8968" originalValue="Carajás">Carajas</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="3442955B30D4AF61079A589672123AD5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M.G. Silva &amp; R. Bahia</emphasis>
2911 MG, FTG, RB); ibid., Serra Norte, 
<emphasis id="C89559972C44F2AD7E511701A7A1D3E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. Cavalcante &amp; M. Silva</emphasis>
2651 (MG); ibid., 
<emphasis id="08015E164B76A09298A2171EE6FEF727" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C.R. Sperling et al.</emphasis>
5584 (MO); ibid., 
<emphasis id="E0938960A4D35A72EC6E537DF849F808" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H.C. de Lima</emphasis>
7099 (RB); Mun. Itaituba, estrada 
<normalizedToken id="5C28DA471ACF03C1273D62500DD96E54" originalValue="Santarém-Cuiabá">Santarem-Cuiaba</normalizedToken>
, BR 163, km 816, Serra do Cachimbo, 
<emphasis id="3A47CB37188278382F0A2369AB9AA28C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I.L. Amaral et al.</emphasis>
1028, (FTG). 
<emphasis id="6875931F2A0F48A25461230EE11ADECD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Tocantins</emphasis>
: Mun. Tocantinopolis, Ribeiro do Corrego, along Belem-Brasilia highway, 
<emphasis id="9F1EC1DBC6E0DAF40773B18516B64EA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">T. Plowman et al.</emphasis>
9250 (MG, FTG).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2EC5362C37AED8A17CE3AA0AB1E85ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="1E2351595EC8D9009EB0B8649EDA3E6D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes</emphasis>
. The erect habit, oblong, shortly petiolate leaves combined with the hypocrateriform vermilion corolla make this species very distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DFE6F80807E7D3D36DF496821D927024" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A hybrid between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="BAA34EB0BA0F69FC28D38D29E63A7779" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marabaensis">
<emphasis id="CE785A4CF828B6B9D207684682EF87A2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea marabaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded and illustrated by 
<normalizedToken id="DE0DE2323DC2E0CBC96F6AD1E87820E6" originalValue="Simão-Bianchini">Simao-Bianchini</normalizedToken>
et al. (2016: 1311).
</paragraph>
